The paper deals with scene understanding in images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel model for generating scene graphs, which involves learning relationships between objects and their attributes, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is based on machine learning techniques, specifically conditional random fields, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves natural language processing, as it aims to generate captions for images, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on three different datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
